#yearofulysses So much of the novel is physicality.  I think with this view (of masturbation) P stays consistent with the rest of the novel.

#yearofulysses Plenty of jokes in U. This I think is not one.

#yearofulysses in fact I find the "he's" usually have pretty clear antecedents from the context/place.

#yearofulysses I've always wondered whether it's really a feminine consc. Joyce is giving us or a male fantasy of it. Did he know?

@Wharfrat1983 @plurabelle #yearofulysses Sometimes an arranger other times a narrator. Kenner's not totally right with U, though.

#yearofulysses As when there are abbreviations meant to be written, not read, like "4d" as a price, when that's not how you'd read it aloud
#yearofulysses What do you think of the relationship b/t M and the "Arranger"? Sometimes the text doesn't read like a monologue
#yearofulysses There are plenty of proper nouns here, and a lot of blurred "he"s, but places and locations are the most vividly described
RT @plurabelle: #yearofulysses J:“[I didnt interpret P] as a human apparition. In conception&technique I depicted the earth which is prehuman&...posthuman”
RT @plurabelle: #yearofulysses There's also the fact that she's drifting off to sleep, and she's ∞, so there's something like a Jungian collective here
@mvp1922 @Wharfrat1983 #yearofulysses Yes, it seems like an odd/disturbing implication when J places the female voice in a totally dif realm
#yearofulysses There's also the fact that she's drifting off to sleep, and she's ∞, so there's something like a Jungian collective here

#yearofulysses "prehuman" makes me think of birth.. P represents the first part of the next day.. June 17th if you will...
#yearofulysses I think the key is that his *conception and technique* are prehuman. All the looping and cyclicality.
